{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"Seems like `getShadowMask()` in `meshlambert_frag.glsl` masks with shadow (in the example case, masks with shadow generated by two point lights).\r\n\r\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/blob\/f3cfc6e4c77e9fb4c111b77c4b9adc2e326b641a\/src\/renderers\/shaders\/ShaderLib\/meshlambert_frag.glsl#L67\r\n\r\nFirst, I'd like to know if this result is actually unexpected. I'm not very familiar with Lambert model with Shadow. Anyone knows about it?","created_at":"2017-10-23T09:09:39.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12457#issuecomment-338596055","id":338596055,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/12457","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMzODU5NjA1NQ==","updated_at":"2017-10-23T09:09:39.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/338596055","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/takahirox\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/takahirox\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/7637832?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/takahirox","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/takahirox\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/takahirox","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/takahirox\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc2Mzc4MzI=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/takahirox\/repos","received_events_url":"htt